begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves. I told her my name and where I'm from, and she told me her name, where she's from, and her family and pets.
middle_memory_text: Various stuff? I told her about Blaseball, how it works, the kinds of things that happen it, on fans voting on the rules for a fictional made up sport, stuff like that.
end_memory_text: It was kind of meta? We talked a bit about the weather and temperature, but also on how long the conversation was, and she mentioned a situation when a conversation froze she had that froze right near the end.
rest_of_day_open: It'll go okay I think? There's a Dungeons & Dragons session tomorrow, I have a couple of internet video watch parties I'm running, I'm trying to help arrange for the gift of a computer for a friend who's sick but is having to use the internet from a cell phone. I have some programming that I really want to do as well.
critical_positive: Well we could see each other, and it helped that we were willing to talk about things. We both spoke English and broadly speaking shared a culture and thus a body of culture references that facilitated conversation. I had a weird thing to talk about that helped me to run out the clock a bit.
critical_negative: Really I had trouble finding things to talk about? I mean, a lot of things that happens just in ordinary life aren't that interested either to talk about or to hear about, and I have problems with things like that when trying to hold up my end of the conversation. I suspect that my partner had similar issues.

begin_memory_text: He proceeded to tell me about some made up game from the internet call blaseball.  He was quite awkward and difficult to talk to.  He just told me a story about this game and how it is the newest craze.
middle_memory_text: I started to realize that we probably have very different political views when he started groaning about the election.  He also started on a rant about how we should care more about the people that are in our jails and their medical care.  I just let him talk.
end_memory_text: He was telling me about the weather in Georgia.  He was also telling me that he doesn't like it there because it is too hot.  He was quite depressing and not very positive throughout the whole conversation.
rest_of_day_open: I hope that this week goes well.  My children have one more in school day and then start a 3 day stretch of virtual instruction.  We are going to show our old house on Friday to potential buyers so I am hoping that goes well.  That will be one less stress off our backs.
critical_positive: We were able to keep the conversation civil.  I pretty much allowed him to talk about the topics he found interesting.  I just nodded and agreed.  I was reaching for straws to find something to talk about with him but it seemed as though we were on 2 different playing fields
critical_negative: He didn't really let me get a word in too much.  He was very awkward and talked about topics that I had no interest in.  He also talked about such specialized areas of expertise that it was hard to follow at times.  I just smiled and nodded hoping that the time would be over.
